bug.short_desc: Virtual: Create list widget with data binding

long_desc.thetext: explore how data binding can be integrated into virtual widgets. We should start with a simple widget like a List.
Created attachment 442 Added a sequance diagramm.
Yes, there is something like a proof of concept but it's nothing more than that as you can see here: http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/demobrowser/index.html#virtual~ListBinding.html
Yes, we already have this list widget. However it's neither complete nor properly documented.

With the beginning of the development of 1.2, we should take care of this bug as soon as possible. Additionally we should completely rethink the current implementation of the virtual list because it still has some issues because we tried to be as API compatible as possible with the non virtual list which is not a good idea. Maybe we should only offer a data binding API for the list.
Johnny will be in charge for that with some help from me.

Hi,
will the virtual widgets be able to load the model remotely on demand? Like the table (using a remote model) does. I couldn't see that from the sequence diagram.

Hey Guilherme, no, the widget will be able to handle data from a qx.data.Array and thats it for the first part. The remote data handling is in my opinion not part of a GUI widget. But we have such a feature on our roadmap for 1.3: http://qooxdoo.org/about/roadmap Regards, Martin
Moving all virtual widget bugs/tasks to Chris.

The first prototype "qx.ui.list.List" implementation is now finished with rev. 22861.
The Demo Browser has two demos List and ExtendedList in the virtual folder which shows the list in action.
The prototype is still in development and will be continued in 1.3.

Finished the implementation for the new virtual list on trunk with the last commit r24235. Only the HTML based rendering is missing at the moment and will be added in a further release. I opened a separate bug report for this enhancement, see bug 4458.
